                        "content": "The nurse is performing an assessment on a client with a diagnosis of Bell's palsy. The nurse would expect to observe which finding in the client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nBell's palsy is a one-sided facial paralysis caused by the compression of the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII). Assessment findings include facial droop from paralysis of the facial muscles; increased lacrimation; painful sensations in the eye, face, or behind the ear; and speech or chewing difficulty. The remaining options are not associated findings in Bell's palsy.",
                        "id": "1fc780c564994b5d873753e0a6f8a9ca",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
